      <h1 class='title'>PENSION LIBERATION: RESTRAINING ORDERS</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 08 July 2004 vol 663 cc186-7GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_186gc' title='Col. 186GC &mdash; HL Deb 08 July 2004 vol 663 c186GC' name='column_186gc' href='#column_186gc' rel='bookmark'>186GC</a>
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_85' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> The Regulator may make a restraining order in relation to an account with a deposit taker if&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_86' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> it is satisfied that the account contains money which has been liberated from a pension scheme,</li>
        <li> it is satisfied that the account is held by or on behalf of&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_87' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> the liberator, or</li>
        <li> a person who has to, or in practice is likely to, ensure that the account is operated in accordance with the liberator's directions, and</li>
        <li> the order is made pending consideration being given to the making of one or more repatriation orders in relation to the account under section (<i>Pension liberation: repatriation orders</i>).</li>
        <li> A restraining order is an order directing that no credit or debit of any amount may be made to the account concerned ("the restrained account") during the period for which the order has effect.</li>
        <li> A restraining order must&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_88' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> specify the name of the deposit taker in respect of which it is made,</li>
        <li> identify the account in respect of which it is made, and</li>
        <li> contain such other information as may be prescribed.</li>
        <li> A restraining order&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_89' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> takes effect when the deposit taker concerned is notified by the Regulator of the making of the order, and</li>
        <li> (subject to subsection (7)) ceases to have effect through expiry of time at the end of the six months beginning with the day when it is made.</li>
        <li> The Regulator may, at a time when a restraining order has effect, make an order extending (or further extending) the restraining order.</li>
        <li> An order under subsection (5) (an "extension order") takes effect&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_90' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> when the deposit taker concerned is notified by the Regulator of the making of the order, but</li>
        <li> only if notification under paragraph (a) occurs at a time when the restraining order concerned has effect.</li>
        <li> Where an extension order takes effect&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_91' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> the restraining order concerned does not cease to have effect through expiry of time until the end of the six months beginning with the time when it would have ceased to have effect through expiry of time had it not been extended, but</li>
        <li> for so long as the extension order has effect, no further extension order can take effect before that time in relation to the restraining order.</li>
        <li> A restraining order does not prevent the crediting to the restrained account of an amount representing interest payable by the deposit taker on any amount which is, or has been, in the account.</li>
        
        <col>GC 187</col>
        <li> Where a restraining order has effect, the deposit taker must return to the payer any money credited to the restrained account in breach of the order.</li>
        <li> Where a restraining order has effect, the Regulator may, on an application made by or with the consent of the person by whom the restrained account is held, by order permit a payment specified in the order to be made out of the account if the Regulator is satisfied&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_92' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> that the payment will be made for the purpose of enabling&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_93' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> any individual to meet his reasonable living expenses, or</li>
        <li> any person to carry on a trade, business, profession or occupation,</li>
        <li> that the beneficial interest in the money out of which the payment will be made belongs&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_94' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> to the individual, or person, concerned, or</li>
        <li> to a person who consents to the making of the payment, and</li>
        <li> that the money out of which the payment will be made is not money liberated from a pension scheme.</li>
        <li> Section 10 of the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-1995">Pensions Act 1995</a> (c. 26) (civil penalties) applies to a deposit taker who, without reasonable excuse, fails to comply with any obligation imposed by a restraining order."</li>
        <li>After Clause 18, insert the following new clause&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
